				\begin{document}$${{\rm{\Delta }}}_{f}=({f}_{early-treatment}-{f}_{pre-treatment})/{f}_{early-treatment}$$\end{document}Δf=(fearly−treatment−fpre−treatment)/fearly−treatmentwhere f is the average value of the feature (PE, WIS, WOS, SER) over the whole tumor. Aggregate features for the pre-treatment and early-treatment images were calculated over FTV1 and FTV2, respectively. This resulted in five imaging features for aggregate analyses. No corresponding aggregate features were calculated for ADI and SRI, as these measure voxel-wise orientational changes captured specifically and only by image registration.
